2004-12-17 15:15 UTC+0700 Budyanto Dj. <budyanto@centrin.net.id>
  * bin/bld.bat
    ! Replace all hbct with ct, hbtip with tip.
      This is in accordance with recent lib renaming.

2004-12-17 15:00 UTC+0700 Budyanto Dj. <budyanto@centrin.net.id>
  * source/rtl/traceprg.prg
    ! File() and FOpen()/FCreate() make different assumptions rgdg path,
      so cFile must contain path to avoid ambiguity.
      If it doesn't, current directory ".\" is added to the front of it.

2004-12-16 23:35 UTC+0100 Przemyslaw Czerpak (druzus/at/priv.onet.pl)
  * xharbour/source/rdd/dbcmd.c
    * removed unnecessary UNLOCK_AREA

  * xharbour/source/rdd/dbf1.c
  * xharbour/source/rdd/dbfcdx/dbfcdx1.c
    * fixed some possible removing of scopes set by scopped relations

2004-12-15 14:40 UTC+0100 Przemyslaw Czerpak (druzus/at/priv.onet.pl)
  * xharbour/make_gnu.sh
    * small modifications to avoid problem when file called '-' exist

  * xharbour/make_tgz.sh
    * fixed HPUX detection

  * xharbour/bin/hb-func.sh
  * xharbour/xharbour.spec
    * changed hbct, hbtip to ct, tip

  * xharbour/contrib/libnf/chdir.c
  * xharbour/contrib/libnf/ftint86.ch
  * xharbour/contrib/libnf/getver.c
  * xharbour/contrib/libnf/mkdir.c
  * xharbour/contrib/libnf/rmdir.c
    * modified for OpenWatcom compilation

  * xharbour/source/rtl/hbcomprs.c
    * replaced MAX() macro by HB_MAX()

  * xharbour/source/rtl/gtsln/gtsln.c
    * removed #if __linux__ for cursor shape setting - it's
      client terminal dependent code not the build platform

  * xharbour/source/ct/files.c
  * xharbour/source/tip/utils.c
    * keep localtime_r under proper macros

  * xharbour/source/vm/itemapi.c
    * HPUX uses isfinite() not finite()

  * xharbour/source/vm/memvars.c
    ! fixed endian dependent code

2004-12-14 21:40 UTC-3 Marcelo Lombardo <marcelo@xharbour.com.br>
  * include/hbsetup.h
    + More HP-UX stuff
  * make_gnu.sh
    + Fixed HP-UX autodetection

2004-12-14 01:10 UTC+0100 Przemyslaw Czerpak (druzus/at/priv.onet.pl)
  * xharbour/make_gnu.sh
  * xharbour/make_tgz.sh
    + added platform autodetection if HB_ARCHITECTURE not set
      and choosing the preferred compiler if HB_COMPILER not set
    + added new platforms (Darwin, SunOS, BSD, HPUX) for info
      descriptions - I do not want to decide if this should be
      also added for make_gnu.bat, make_gnu.cmd because these
      files cannot be used for this platforms.
      Now make_bsd.sh, make_drw.sh, make_hp.sh, make_mingw.sh are
      redundant - we should decide if they should be kept in CVS
      or removed. Probably some modifications for MINGW and
      HPUX will be necessary.

  * harbour/make_tgz.sh
    + added platform autodetection if HB_ARCHITECTURE not set
      and choosing the preferred compiler if HB_COMPILER not set

  * xharbour/bin/hb-func.sh
    * some small modification for 'tr' versions which need []
      for character range definition

  * xharbour/include/hbdefs.h
    * minor modification of typo in commented code

  * xharbour/source/rdd/dbf1.c
  * xharbour/source/rdd/dbfcdx/dbfcdx1.c
    * minor cleaning and casting

  * xharbour/source/vm/extend.c
  * xharbour/source/vm/itemapi.c
    * fixed some minor typos in GCC hack

2004-12-13 10:10 UTC-0300 Walter Negro <anegro-AT-overnet.com.ar>
  * source/vm/thread.c
    ! Fix compilation problem in Linux

2004-12-12 03:40 UTC-300 Walter Negro <anegro-AT-overnet.com.ar>
  * source/vm/hash.c
    ! Fixed incorrect comparison in hb_hashPreallocate
    ! Fixed parameters calling to error functions.
  * source/vm/thread.c
    + Add function HB_MUTEXTIMEOUTLOCK.
       This funcion try to lock a mutex with timeout, if success return .T.,
        if timeout occurrr return .F.

2004-12-11 22:00 UTC-0800 Brian Hays <bhays@abacuslaw.com>
  * contrib/rdd_ads/ads1.c
    * fixed dbInfo
      case DBI_ISREADONLY:
      case DBI_LOCKCOUNT:
      case DBI_ALIAS:
      case DBI_FCOUNT:
      case DBI_FOUND:
      case DBI_DBFILTER:
      case DBI_EOF:
      case DBI_BOF:
      case DBI_CHILDCOUNT:
      case DBOI_POSITION (to support passing a new value)
         also "fixes" ordKeyGoTo
         notice ADS does not have a KeyGoTo function so this was implemented
         via GoTop and Skip and is not guaranteed to be fast.
         PLEASE use ads[G|S]etRelKeyPos() for scrollbars!

      case DBOI_ISDESC
         was already supported to return the value.
         ads does not support dynamic switching of the descend flag.

  * contrib/rdd_ads/adsfunc.c
    * added HB_FUNC( ADSISRECORDVALID )
         Returns: Does current record match current filter?
         Useful after setting a filter to decide if GoTop is required to
            be on a valid record; or if after a dbGoTo to know if on a valid record.
         Eventually this should be replaced by a generic rdd call.

  * doc/hbi18n.txt
    * minor typo tweaks

2004-12-10 23:15 UTC-0500 Paul Tucker <ptucker@sympatico.ca>
  * source/rtl/winreg.prg
    * added a few casts.
  * source/rtl/gtapi.c
    * added some (BOOL) casts that the compiler should not be
    * complaining about

2004-12-11 01:30 UTC+0100 Przemyslaw Czerpak (druzus/at/priv.onet.pl)
  * xharbour/include/hbapi.h
  * xharbour/include/hbdefs.h
  * xharbour/include/hbstack.h
   * changed the multi command macro definitions to use do {...} while(0)
     for safe use in any C statement

  * xharbour/source/vm/hvm.c
    * some other optimisations and some of them suggested by Paul - thanks.

  * xharbour/source/rtl/gtcrs/gtcrs.h
    * formatting

  * xharbour/source/rdd/dbf1.c
   ! fixed the bug in pack I introduced in previous commit

  * xharbour/source/rdd/dbffpt/dbffpt1.c
   ! fixed opening FPT files in READONLY mode on POSIX systems

2004-12-10 21:25 UTC-300 Eduardo Fernandes <modalsist@yahoo.com.br>

  * utils/hbmake/hbmake.prg
  * utils/hbmake/hbmutils.prg
    ! hbct.lib, hbctmt.lib, hbtip.lib and hbtipmt were renamed to
      ct.lib, ctmt.li tip.lib and tipmt.lib respectively, in accordance
      with recent changes. Now these libs will be compiled together with
      default libs and not with external libs. Please, recreate yours
      *.bc makefiles to avoid errors.

