2004-12-02 04:25 UTC+0100 Przemyslaw Czerpak (druzus/at/priv.onet.pl)
  * xharbour/bin/hb-func.sh
    + added -xbgtk switch for easy linking with Phil's xbgtk lib

  * xharbour/include/hbrdddbf.h
  * xharbour/source/rdd/dbf1.c
    + added SELF_GETREC() methods
    * change DBF RDD internals to call SELF_{GET,PUT}REC() method
      for internal direct record reading/writing with NULL buffer
      pointer - for future use with CRYPT RDD
    ! replaced some direct calls to hb_dbf*() functions with proper
      methods - it could cause troubles for some upper level RDDs
      which need control over such methods

  * xharbour/source/rtl/gtapi.c
    ! fixed the problem caused by incompatibilities between
      screen functions in CT for Window 0 - it works a little bit
      differ

  * xharbour/source/vm/memvars.c
    * temporary disabled (waiting for a global fix) the line which
      fixes the memory leaks but can cause memvar item clearing in
      some cases.
      IMHO memory leak is better then RT error.

  * xharbour/include/hbstack.h
  * xharbour/source/vm/asort.c
  * xharbour/source/vm/estack.c
  * xharbour/source/vm/fastitem.c
  * xharbour/source/vm/hvm.c
    + added some simple hacks with inlining some very often used
      functions by macros and some small improvements in most often
      executed places - it gives nearly 10% speed up on PCODE evaluation.

